## Use Cases

### API Documentation

TSDoc comments are converted to mdz at build time by `tsdoc_helpers.ts`:

```typescript
/**
 * Parses mdz content and returns an AST.
 *
 * @param content - The mdz string to parse
 * @returns Array of `Mdz_Node` representing the parsed content
 */
export function mdz_parse(content: string): Mdz_Node[] {
  // ...
}
```

At build time, TSDoc link syntax converts to mdz:
- `{@link url|text}` → `[text](url)`
- `{@link https://...}` → `https://...`
- `{@link identifier}` → `` `identifier` ``

At runtime, `` `identifier` `` auto-links to API docs when available.

### Documentation Pages

Manual documentation written in mdz (like this file):

- Simple syntax for nontechnical writers
- Whitespace preservation for code examples
- Auto-linking to API identifiers
- Svelte component integration

### Component Descriptions

Describing component behavior with auto-linked code:

```
This component accepts a `status` prop and renders an `Alert`.
See `Alert.svelte` for the full API.
```

### Inline Help Text

Lightweight formatting without markdown complexity:

```
**Important:** Make sure to call `cleanup()` when done.
```

