## Implementation Details

### Parser Architecture

**File:** `src/lib/mdz.ts` (1614 lines)

**Characteristics:**
- Single-pass lexer/parser
- Character-code-based scanning for performance
- Text accumulation optimization
- Strict validation (false negatives over false positives)
- Greedy/bounded delimiter matching (prevents nested formatters from consuming parent delimiters)
- Position tracking for all nodes

### Renderer Components

**`Mdz.svelte`** - Component wrapper that parses content and renders nodes

**`Mdz_Node_View.svelte`** - Renders individual AST nodes recursively

**Basic usage:**

```svelte
<script>
  import Mdz from '@ryanatkn/fuz/Mdz.svelte';
</script>

<Mdz content="**Bold** and _italic_ text." />
```

**Advanced usage with direct parsing:**

```svelte
<script>
  import {mdz_parse} from '@ryanatkn/fuz/mdz.js';
  import Mdz_Node_View from '@ryanatkn/fuz/Mdz_Node_View.svelte';

  const nodes = mdz_parse(content);
</script>

<div class="custom white_space_pre_wrap">
  {#each nodes as node}
    <Mdz_Node_View {node} />
  {/each}
</div>
```

### Context System

**`mdz_components_context`** - Register Svelte components

**`mdz_elements_context`** - Register HTML elements

Both accept `Map<string, any>` or Svelte's `SvelteMap`.

### TSDoc Integration

**Build phase** (`tsdoc_helpers.ts`):
- Extracts JSDoc/TSDoc from TypeScript source
- Converts TSDoc link syntax to mdz format
- Stores as mdz strings in generated package metadata

**Runtime phase**:
- mdz parser processes the strings
- Backtick code auto-links to API identifiers
- Links render to `/docs/api` routes

